        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 24 at 2:15PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 215 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Aurora, or 14 miles east of Denver, moving northeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Landspouts, wind gusts up to 40 mph, and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible. Gusty winds
could knock down tree limbs and blow around unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Aurora, northeastern Centennial, Arapahoe Park and Buckley SFB.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.

If a tornado is spotted seek shelter inside a sturdy building.</instruction>
